tags.description: a long green field park besides maujpur road

The Najafgarh Nallah is a channelized waterway that was once a part of the Sahibi River and an elongation of the Najafgarh Jheel Lake. It flows through rural southwest Delhi and ultimately outfalls into the Yamuna River.
